          "date": "2013-09-04 16:21:57.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-3336 lfsck: user space tools for orphan handling",
        "message": "LU-3336 lfsck: user space tools for orphan handling\n\nOffer some user space tools to allow the administrator to process\nthe orphan under /lost+found.\n\nIn former LFSCK patches, the LFSCK will create the lost MDT-object\nunder /lost+found. The LFSCK cannot further process the MDT-object\nunder /lost+found becuase it has limited knowledge about where the\noriginal file located. Then it is the administrator's duty to help\nthe recovery.\n\n1) list_orphans\n   List orphans on the specified MDT.\n   usage: lfs list_orphans <mount_point> <MDT_index>\n\n2) stat_orphan\n   Stat the specified orphan on the specified MDT.\n   usage: lfs stat_orphan <mount_point> <MDT_index> <orphan_name>\n\n3) move_orphan\n   Move the specified orphan to normal visible namespace.\n   Do NOT allow to replace an existing file with the orphan.\n   usage: lfs move_orphan <mount_point> <MDT_index> <orphan_name>\n          <target>\n\nTest-Parameters: testlist=sanity-lfsck\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I15b80297c0c9b93e95ab9d31fc0af7f4447a156e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
